1. Prompt the user for R, P, S input
2. Check to make sure that the input is valid. If not, go to step 8.
3. Have the program pick a random value from a list of possible values
4. Compare the user input value to that of the randomly chosen value
5. Display the randomly selected value as the computer's choice
6. Display the result of comparing the values
7. Increment the appropriate value tracking wins, losses, or ties
8. Display a running total of wins, losses, and ties
9. Ask the user if they want to play again. If yes, return to Step 1